programme.sub-title: South Africa v Pakistan: Second Test Day Two
programme.desc: South Africa v Pakistan. Coverage of the second day of the second test in the three-match series from Newlands Cricket Ground in Cape Town. The hosts have an excellent recent test record at this venue, winning nine, drawing three and losing just one of their 13 matches played here over the last 10 years. programme.title: Live NBA: Dallas @ Boston
programme.desc: Boston Celtics v Dallas Mavericks (Tip-off 1.00am). Coverage of the inter-conference clash from TD Garden. Dirk Nowitzki recently set an NBA record when he returned from injury to play his first match of the campaign for the Mavericks, becoming the first player in history to represent the same team in 21 seasons. While his best days are behind him the German is a certainty to be inducted into the Hall of Fame once his career comes to an end, and attention is already turning towards his teammate Luka Doncic, who is being hailed as a future league MVP even though he is only a few months into his rookie season.(n)

programme.title: Live One-Day International Cricket
programme.sub-title: New Zealand v Sri Lanka: Second ODI
programme.desc: New Zealand v Sri Lanka. Coverage of the second one-day international in the three-match series from Bay Oval, Tauranga. New Zealand claimed victory by 36 runs in the only pervious meeting between the sides here in this format in 2016, but the Black Caps have tasted defeat in the other three 50-over matches they have played here, losing to England last February and twice against South Africa in 2014.(n)

programme.title: NBA: Oklahoma City - Dallas
